The account type is an attribute attached to the account that will impact the way accounting documents will be printed or filtered. Account Types are as follow : asset, cash, commitment, current asset (stock), debt, equity, expense, immobilisation, income, payable, provision, receivable, special, tax, view
The account code is usually a number (e.g. : 101000). The account code help to locate the account in the chart of account. This code must be unique per company account chart.
Each account is linked to a chart of account, and thus to a company.
Le compte parent permet de définir la hiérarchie du compte dans le plan comptable de la société.
